# Phase 03 / Cycle 1 RED — Two-tenant deployment reproduction (blocked)
#
# Persona: Writer (Opus 4.7)
# Date: 2026-05-29
# Frozen FraiseQL SHA: d0a4ed4ec1770c70707f68fd9019f2b561d87461 (v2.3.2)
# Target page: /building/multi-tenancy
#
# Goal (Cycle-1 RED bullet 2): "Configure a two-tenant deployment via
# `PUT /api/v1/admin/tenants/foo` and `bar`; issue queries through both
# with the same JWT; observe behaviour."
#
# Status: BLOCKED in this RED pass. The off-the-shelf `fraiseql-server`
# binary (frozen-SHA Cycle-2 image) cannot host the documented two-tenant
# deployment workflow end-to-end. Two independent blockers:
#
#   BLOCKER #1 — Admin API path is not auto-wired by the binary.
#       `crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/state.rs:L10-L181`
#       (`build_app_state()`) never installs a `TenantExecutorRegistry`, a
#       `TenantExecutorFactory`, or a `DomainRegistry`. The admin tenant
#       handlers (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/routes/api/tenant_admin.rs`
#       L160-L283) require all three. Even if `admin_api_enabled = true` and
#       `admin_token` is set, `PUT /api/v1/admin/tenants/foo` returns
#       `404 multi-tenant mode not enabled` because
#       `state.tenant_registry()` is `None`.
#
#       Reproduced under BLOCKER #1 below: a sidecar fraiseql-server with
#       `admin_api_enabled = true` + `admin_token = "..."` boots, but fails
#       startup with an unrelated RBAC-schema error (see BLOCKER #2). Even
#       had it booted, the tenant admin path would 404.
#
#   BLOCKER #2 — `admin_api_enabled = true` requires RBAC schema
#       initialization that fails on a clean Postgres database with a SQL
#       syntax error from the docs-test schema fixture set.
#
#       Reproduced literally: setting `admin_api_enabled = true` (with
#       `admin_token`) causes the server to bail at startup with
#       `Configuration error: Failed to initialize RBAC schema: Query error:
#       Schema creation failed: error returned from database: syntax error
#       at or near "("`. This is a docs-harness fixture problem (the harness
#       does not pre-seed an RBAC-compatible schema) NOT a framework bug.
#       The Cycle-5 smoke fixture seeds a hand-rolled User/Post schema
#       (`fixtures/postgres/_smoke.compiled.json`) that does not include
#       the RBAC management bootstrap. The GREEN Writer / Cleanup will need
#       to either:
#           (a) ship a `multi-tenancy.toml` overlay that disables the RBAC
#               management API path while still enabling tenant admin
#               routes, OR
#           (b) extend the harness with an `[rbac]` bootstrap fixture, OR
#           (c) document the two-tenant deployment workflow as a
#               library-level recipe (calling `with_tenant_registry` from a
#               host binary that wraps `fraiseql-server`) rather than as a
#               curl-against-the-binary recipe, which is what the existing
#               framework integration test does
#               (`crates/fraiseql-server/tests/multitenancy_test.rs`).
#
# Source citations:
#   - tenant admin handler 404 path:
#     crates/fraiseql-server/src/routes/api/tenant_admin.rs:L160-L283
#   - registry default is None:
#     crates/fraiseql-server/src/routes/graphql/app_state.rs:L101-L180
#   - registry never installed by the binary:
#     crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/state.rs:L10-L181
#   - integration test wires the registry programmatically:
#     crates/fraiseql-server/tests/multitenancy_test.rs:L107-L130 (helper)
#
# Reproduction shell (run from ~/code/fraiseql-docs/scripts/docs-test):

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

