# Step 3 — what the framework's own multitenancy_test.rs does (library API):

# crates/fraiseql-server/tests/multitenancy_test.rs:107-130 (helper)
#
#   fn make_multitenant_state() -> AppState<StubAdapter> {
#       let state = AppState::new(Arc::new(Executor::new(
#           CompiledSchema::default(),
#           Arc::new(StubAdapter::new("default")),
#       )));
#       let registry = TenantExecutorRegistry::new(state.executor.clone());
#       state.with_tenant_registry(Arc::new(registry))
#   }
#
# Tests then call `registry.upsert("tenant-a", ...)` and
# `registry.upsert("tenant-b", ...)` directly. There is NO HTTP-API surface
# in those tests — they exercise the registry as a Rust API.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

What this reproduction proves vs. what the Cycle-1 phase-doc claims:

1. CONFIRMED at library level: `TenantExecutorRegistry::upsert(...)` is the
   admission point for new tenants. The admin REST routes
   (`PUT /api/v1/admin/tenants/{key}` etc.) are the HTTP facade for the same
   operation (tenant_admin.rs:L160-L283 calls
   `registry.upsert_with_quota(...)`).

2. DRIFT vs. phase-doc Cycle-1 bullets — the admin REST API:
       PUT/DELETE /api/v1/admin/tenants/{key}
       GET        /api/v1/admin/tenants
       GET        /api/v1/admin/tenants/{key}/health
       PUT/DELETE /api/v1/admin/domains/{domain}
       GET        /api/v1/admin/domains
   is mounted by the binary's `mount_admin_api()` ONLY when:
     (i)  `admin_api_enabled = true` AND `admin_token` is set, AND
     (ii) `AppState::tenant_registry` is `Some(...)`.

   Condition (ii) is never satisfied by the binary at the frozen SHA. The
   Writer GREEN draft must either pivot to "library API + host binary"
   framing or block on a framework feature request.

3. DRIFT vs. phase-doc Cycle-1 bullet "v2.3 hardening additions":
   `TenancyConfig` / `TenancyMode` settings live on the *compiled schema*
   (`security.tenancy` block — security_config.rs:L113-L186), NOT on the
   server TOML. They are produced by `fraiseql-cli compile` from
   `[fraiseql.tenancy]` in `fraiseql.toml`. The docs-test image does NOT
   ship the `fraiseql` CLI binary (see `Dockerfile.fraiseql`'s
   `CARGO_FEATURES` block which builds `fraiseql-server` only). The GREEN
   Writer must show this via either (a) a hand-rolled compiled schema with
   `security.tenancy.mode = "row"`, (b) a sidecar CLI container, or
   (c) document the CLI's output shape without a runnable exercise.

4. Additional framework finding to surface to Bug-Finder (next session):
   `admin_api_enabled = true` causes startup failure when the database does
   not have the RBAC management schema. This was observed against the
   docs-test Postgres fixture in this RED pass. May be a docs-harness
   fixture gap, may be a framework bug (server should not refuse to boot
   when RBAC bootstrap fails — degrade RBAC routes only). Bug-Finder owns
   the call.
